A 'Turdus merula' is a species of blackbird, belonging to the thrush family.
It has a glossy black plumage with an orange-yellow eye-ring and bill.
Its feathers are sleek and well-groomed giving it a very distinct appearance.
The males have a striking yellow beak, while the females have a more subtle brownish-yellow beak.
It has a slim, oval-shaped body with a long tail, and can grow up to 25 cm in length.
'Turdus merulas' are commonly found across Europe and Asia, as well as North Africa and have adapted to both urban and rural areas.
They are known to sing beautiful and complex melodies and are often found in gardens, parks, woodlands, and hedgerows.
